thread.title_full: Offensive player of the week (9/21): Sachse's Jalen Mayden | Dallas Morning News

author: Michael Florek
title: Offensive player week (9/21): Sachse's Jalen Mayden
text:
Jalen Mayden; Sachse
What he did: Mayden completed 29 of 34 passes for 545 yards and six touchdowns while rushing 12 times for 73 yards and one touchdown in Sachse's 66-41 win over Tyler Lee in the team's District 11-6A opener. Sachse trailed 41-31 in the third quarter, but Mayden threw five straight touchdown passes (from 65, 69, 46, 62 and 52 yards out) to put give Sachse 35 unanswered points.
Who is he? A 6-2, 205-pound sophomore quarterback.
The stats: Mayden has completed 58 of his 77 passes (75 percent) on the year for 1,030 yards, 12 touchdowns and three interceptions. He also has 40 carries for 281 yards and one touchdown.
He said it: "Really just the receivers got open. Once they got downfield they read the safeties and made the right reads and I got them the ball."
Coach said it: "A year ago today, he was down there with the freshman. It's a whole different ballgame when you move up to the varsity level. He's making that adjustment ... That's a big jump, you look out there, you see a 6-2, 205 body, or however tall he is, he walks to the sideline takes his helmet off, he's just a young guy. You forget that sometimes." - Mark Behrens
Did you know? Jalen is the brother of former Sachse receiver/cornerback James Mayden and current Sachse senior cornerback Jared Mayden. James is now a sophomore receiver at Rice, while Jared is a four-star recruit pledged to Oregon. Jalen already has offers from Houston, Oregon State and Syracuse and is looking at a number of other schools including Baylor, Miami, Oklahoma and Texas. ... Jalen is also a point guard for the basketball team and a member of the track team, running the 100 meters, 200 meters and 4x100 meters.
